properties.abstract: Foostock is a little detour from Foopass, which links (or separates) the cantons of Glarus and St. Gall. Foopass is reached on the Sardona World Heritage Trail from Elm (route 73 by Wanderland Schweiz). The area is famous for the Glarus Thrust, which reveals the processes forming mountains. On the ascent to Foopass this is less the subject than the length and wildness of the gorge along which the hiking trail winds its way up to Alp Ramin and further on to Foopass. From there up to Foostöckli the terrain is gentle. If you want to visit its bigger brother summit behind, you need to take a test of courage on a steep path. There, nothing is in the way of the splendid view to Chrauchtal or Weisstannental and beyond.
properties.subtitle: No "faux pas" on the Foopass
properties.title: From Elm via Foopass

sac_photos.title: Behind Fahnenstock the Ringelspitz range is visible.
Foostock has a little brother, Foostöckli.

segments.description: From Elm follow the hiking trail Nr. 73 in the gorge of Raminerbach to Alp Ramin. Continue to Foopass via Mittler Stafel and Raminer Matt. From there follow a grassy, increasingly steep ridge to the foot of Foostöckli.
segments.title: Elm - Foopass – foot of Foostöckli

segments.description: 50 m below Foostöckli a distinct path traverses the north face, for a short while on steep terrain. Then the terrain transforms into a large ridge which leads to the summit structure of Foostock. Now on a good path hike to the summit, passing a narrow passage.
segments.title: Foopass - Foostock

segments.description:
From Foopass continue to Weisstannen: T2, 2½–3 h. 
On week-ends in the summer season there is a bus starting at Vorsiez.
segments.title: Variant: descent to Weisstannental
